issue.title: Add OS security patch level to default tags
issue.body:
### Problem Statement

There are security patches from OS vendors, that break critical parts of the storage and break librarires and apps. It happened recently with a security patch from Samsung. See more info [here](https://github.com/oblador/react-native-keychain/issues/617).

### Solution Brainstorm

In order to investigate this type of issues, it's valuable to have OS security patch level reported to sentry tags. We've now added it manually on our side, but I think it would be great to have it by default coming from Sentry.

### Product Area

Issues

issue.title: Allow "Additional data" (extra) to be displayed in Slack integration notification
issue.body: ### Problem Statement I want to be able to send additional data from an event and have it showing up in Slack directly, for quicker triages. Example: ``` Sentry.captureMessage('Test 1', { extra: { test: 'test', now: Date.now(), now_iso: new Date(), }, }); ``` Which displays in Sentry here: But nothing appears in Slack, I even tried to set the tags option in the alerts notification to include `extra`, but I think it's considered something else and not really a tag internally. ### Solution Brainstorm It would be nice to have an option where it would be displayed, even if it's under a 3-backtick markdown block. ### Product Area Alerts

commits.message: fix(source-map-debugger): Normalize source map reference headers before access (#58680)
feat(events-stats): Add support for comparison in metrics timeseries queries (#58587)
feat(inbound-filters) Add edge legacy option to legacy-browser inbound filters, (back-end) (#58606)

fix(notifications): use html template instead of dynamic html params where needed (#58658) After releasing https://github.com/getsentry/sentry/pull/58227, some email notifications become broken. Example: The cause is that `format_html` escaped template parameters that contained HTML code in cases such as: ``` html_params["version"] = f'{escape(self.version_parsed)}' ``` From security perspective, this was kinda correct behavior, since parameter contains untrusted HTML. When building HTML, we should use HTML-specific templates instead. This PR: * Updates the signature of the `get_description()` method in the base GroupActivityNotification class and in all inherited classes: * old output: template, parameters, html_parameters (optional) * new output: text_template, html_template (optional), parameters * The set of parameters would be the same for both modes -- text and HTML * But we are going to redefine HTML template where needed. * Redefines HTML templates for two cases: * RegressionActivityNotification (fixes the above bug) -- we want to render release link as `` tag * ResolvedInReleaseActivityNotification -- same * The HTML template for most of cases is None and therefore normal text template is used.
Revert "Revert "fix(crons): Correctly compute next_checkin for tz aware monitors (#58550)"" (#58686)
fix(ddm): use 10s granularity only for custom metrics (#58688)

Renamed 'account number' to correct name 'Account ID' (#58320)

In AWS it is called `Account ID` and not `Account number`.
Renamed all visible occurrences in AWS Lambda integration.
feat(inbound-filters) Add edge legacy option to legacy-browser inbound filters (front-end) (#58600)
fix(alerts): use metrics enhanced dataset (#58681)

feat(hybridcloud) Make error embed view use region URLs v2  (#58660)

Mulligan on https://github.com/getsentry/sentry/pull/58608 as those
changes imported a dev dependency which
doesn't exist in production builds.

This reverts commit
https://github.com/getsentry/sentry/commit/17daa1f4ef4ef6f0a4abcd3ce567424f7fab550b
and doesn't include the problematic import.

tests(hybrid-cloud): Stabilize slack webhook tests (#58691)

Tagged most of these tests as `region_silo_test` since that is the silo
where the business logic will actually execute. Had to break out the
`IdentityView` tests though since they are returned from the control
silo.
fix(alerts): flag check (#58692)

feat(replay): Put "beta" badge on the Selectors tab label, instead of the page title (#58645)

Translate the "Replays" and "Selectors" tabs on the replay index page.

also refactored the path/url stuff to remove string concatenation.
Should be easier to spot the urls if someone's browsing through the
codebase.

tests(hybrid-cloud): Stabilize Bitbucket Parser tests (#58693)

Used `eu` as a key for a missing region, but didn't override the region
config for the testcase. Resolved for Bitbucket and Bitbucket Server.

fix(provisioning): user id instead of email for partner user (#58672)

Before we got an email and found the user from that email which is
really not necessary. This is one specific user for each partner, let's
store user_id instead and get directly to user from id.
ref(feedback): bring back tags in feedback details (#58673) some tags are back! others, like `locale`, `replay,` and `platform`, are unavailable right now though

meta(routing) Sync with product-owners.yml in security-as-code@de0b0fe7 (#58698)

Syncing with
[product-owners.yml](https://github.com/getsentry/security-as-code/blob/de0b0fe73661bf71412f7cb7377f37a6460df6fb/rbac/lib/product-owners.yml)
([docs](https://www.notion.so/473791bae5bf43399d46093050b77bf0)).

---------

Co-authored-by: getsantry[bot] <getsantry[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>
Co-authored-by: Hubert Deng <hubert.deng@sentry.io>

ref(backup): Simplify some import logic (#58628)

Some of the user model logic was very difficult to follow, which this PR
aims to simplify. In essence, there were too many placed where we marked
models `ImportKind.Existing`, when really they should just be
`ImoportKind.Inserted` due to `post_save` shenanigans.

Additionally, `UserPermission` and `UserEmail` logic has been cleaned up
and looks more uniform now, and comments have been added where things
get a bit subtle.
ref(bug reports): remove display of name for now (#58659)

feat(feedback): Remove old feedback widget and replace with SDK version (#58305)

This will be disabled until we add the feedback widget in getsentry.
use f-strings
